Example using an Xbox One controller's joysticks, buttons, and triggers with
GLFW, adapted from the "wave.c" example included with GLFW. Also supports mouse
and keyboard movement

Edit the Makefile as needed, and build using "make"

Make sure to have glfw, glad, tinycthread, and linmath installed or build
somewhere, as well as pthread Links to each of these git repos are below. They
may also be included with the glfw soure. Edit the makefile to include each of
these in the include and linking paths

glfw
https://github.com/glfw/glfw

glad
https://github.com/Dav1dde/glad

tinycthread
https://github.com/tinycthread/tinycthread

linmath
https://github.com/datenwolf/linmath.h


